          <from>THE PREMIER</from>
          <p>THE PREMIER : Mr. Speaker, as you would know, and all members of this House would know, this is the third potential labour disruption that we've had in this province with different unions, different employers, and each time we've come to the point where we've ended up trying to - we're now discussing what an emergency is and what isn't. This bill clearly lays out steps that will put in place essential services legislation that will move forward.</p>
        </speech>
