          <p>MR. FUREY : Mr. Speaker, as of today, officially, the Department of Municipal Affairs. I just want to follow up on the question of my colleague in Opposition. Over the last three months, we've had extensive discussions, and there is a combination of factors. But it's safe to say that the leadership in our municipal governments are openly discussing amalgamation and it's not the dirty word that it used to be only a few short years ago.</p>
